rooms.Name: The Beginning of the Light Woods
rooms.Description:
You blink quickly and realize the woods are now somehow differant. You feel
as if you are no longer where you were a moment ago. You decide to shrug this
feeling off and continue your exploration of the forest.

rooms.Name: Among the Trees of the Light Forest
rooms.Description:
You are here among the many trees of the lighter portion of Darkendale
Forest. Everything seems so peaceful and serene. You see animals scurry about
the ground in search of food. Leaves rustle here and there as a soft breeze
blows through the trees. You like this place, but something doesn't feel
quite right, kind of like you're not the only intelligent being in the woods.

rooms.Name: Among the Trees of the Light Forest
rooms.Description:

Forest. Everything seems so peaceful and serene. You see animals scurry about
the ground in search of food. Leaves rustle here and there as a soft breeze
blows through the trees. You like this place, but something doesn't feel
quite right, kind of like you're not the only intelligent being in the woods.
You appear to be standing at a junction of paths in the woods.

rooms.Name: Among the Trees of the Light Forest
rooms.Description:

rooms.Name: Next to a Pond in the Light Woods
rooms.Description:
You are here among the many trees of the lighter portion of Darkendale
Forest. Everything seems so peaceful and serene. You see animals scurry about
the ground in search of food. Leaves rustle here and there as a soft breeze
blows through the trees. You like this place, but something doesn't feel
quite right, kind of like you're not the only intelligent being in the woods.
Directly next to you, you see a small clear pond. The occasional fish jumps
out of the water disturbing it's glasslike surface. You kind of wish you
could take a swim, but considering you know nothing about this place, you opt
not to risk it.

rooms.Name: Among the Trees of the Light Forest
rooms.Description:

quite right, kind of like you're not the only intelligent being in the woods.
The path leads both north and east here. Hmm.....Which way to go?

Hmmm...It appears as if you've hit a dead end, but for some reason you don't

Exits.Description:
You look up to see a walkway spanning the trees' branches. In it's bottom
here you see a trap door.

rooms.Name: Among the Trees of the Light Forest

Forest. Everything seems so peaceful and serene. You see animals scurry about

quite right, kind of like you're not the only intelligent being in the woods.
It seems as though you've come to a fork in the road. So is it east or west?

rooms.Name: Among the Trees of the Light Forest
rooms.Description:

Forest. Everything seems so peaceful and serene. You see animals scurry about
the ground in search of food. Leaves rustle here and there as a soft breeze
blows through the trees. You like this place, but something doesn't feel
quite right, kind of like you're not the only intelligent being in the woods.
Drat! Another dead end! Time to turn around.....*sigh*

rooms.Name: Among the Trees of the Light Forest
rooms.Description:
You are here among the many trees of the lighter portion of Darkendale
Forest. Everything seems so peaceful and serene. You see animals scurry about
the ground in search of food. Leaves rustle here and there as a soft breeze
blows through the trees. You like this place, but something doesn't feel
quite right, kind of like you're not the only intelligent being in the woods.
The path goes north from here....though I don't think it's a good idea. The
woods seem to get really dark and spooky to the north. Maybe you should turn
around.

rooms.Name: Among the Trees of the Dark Forest
rooms.Description:
You look around and overwhelming sense of terror grips your body. You don't
like this place, you don't like it at all. The shadows about you seems to be
moving...living...creatures. You hear strange noises coming from the
darkness. Gossebumps stud every inch of your skin. It's not possible for you
to be anymore afraid. You have to try desperately to resist the urge to run.

rooms.Name: Entering the Cave
rooms.Description:
You slowly decend into the cave, all the while it grows impossibly more dark
then it already was. A dank, musky smell meets your nose, the smell of
animals, you also recognize another smell in the air...rotten flesh. Your
heart hammers on the inside of your chest. The walls about you seem to move,
but it's just your imagination.....or is it? You still can't see the cave
floor.

rooms.Name: Bottom of the Shaft
rooms.Description:
Your feet finally touch solid ground and you exhale a small sigh of relief,
but then you hear a low growl. Maybe you were better off up there. Too late
to turn back now. What ever it is you will have to fight it off. You take a
deep breath and search for an exit to this chamber.

rooms.Name: Inside the Caves
rooms.Description:
You are now inside a long narrow passage. You have to grope along the walls
just to make sure you don't walk into one of them. The overwhelming smell of
animal fills your nose, making you wanna be sick. You foot happens to kick
something, something hard, something long, something...white. You stifle an
impulse to vomit. You keep moving.

rooms.Name: Intersection of Passages in the Caves
rooms.Description:
Tunnels branch off in all directions here. You can't figure out which way to
go. You wish you could see the tunnels better, but it's just too frigging
dark to see almost anything. I suppose you'll just have to guess. Again you
hear a low growl in the darkness. I'd make up my mind pretty quickly if I
were you.

rooms.Name: Next to an Underground Cliff
rooms.Description:
You grope around for something to hold onto, but can't find anything. You see
nothing but a pool of darkness next to you. You can just make it out as a
cliff ledge. You can't guess how far it is to the bottom. I'd be careful if I
were you.

rooms.Name: Split of Passages
rooms.Description:
The passage branches off both north and east here. Again you are presented
with the irritating choice, which way to go? You wouldn't happen to have a
quarter on you, would you?

rooms.Name: Narrow Passage
rooms.Description:
There is just barely shoulder space in this part of the passage, but then
again, that's nothing new. You squeeze along trying not to trip over anything
in the darkness. Your hands occasionally brush against a wet spot on the
wall...what it is you don't know, and probably don't want to.

rooms.Name: Bottom of Drop Off
rooms.Description:
OUCH!!!!! THAT REALLY HURT! At least you survived the fall, I hope. You make
a mental note to be a little more careful as to where you're going next time.
Nothing to do now but gather your energy and climb up the rock face.

rooms.Name: Top of a Downward Shaft
rooms.Description:
You see a large opening in the floor here. You peer into it, but can't make
anything out. There is a strong smell of death down there. You hear some
chewing noises coming from down within the opening. Maybe you should check it
out.....or not.

rooms.Name: Bottom of Another Shaft
rooms.Description:
Again you breath a sigh of relief as your feet strike hard ground. The smell
of rotten flesh is particularly strong here. Maybe you don't want to see
whats in the next chamber......

rooms.Name: Dining "Room"
rooms.Description:
Chewed up corpses litter the ground everywhere. There are bones, arms, feet,
and other various parts and organs lying about. This must be primarily where
the monsters eat. You can't help it this time.....you throw up.

rooms.Name: Dead End
rooms.Description:
The passage terminates into a rock wall here. A dead end. As you glance
around you realize just how literal that is. Some poor person's corpse is
lying here, the flesh rotting away. Time to turn around I'd say.

rooms.Name: Winding Passageway
rooms.Description:
The passage twists and turns in every direction. You have to keep your arms
in front of you at all times in order to keep yourself from hitting a wall.
But even that doesnt work all the time.

rooms.Name: Winding Passageway
rooms.Description:
The passage continues to wind it's way seemingly in circles. You really hope
this will end soon. You've already got about 8 bumps on your head from
running into walls.

rooms.Name: Top of a Large Opening
rooms.Description:
You finally make your way out of the passage only to find yourself face to
face with a big hole in the cave floor. Oh hell, you've come this far, you
might as well see whats down there.

rooms.Name: Inside the Hole
rooms.Description:
You climb down the shaft, occasionally cutting your hand on a sharp rock
sticking out from the shaft wall. Damn, this one seems pretty deep.

rooms.Name: Further Down the Hole
rooms.Description:
You're still climbing.....You're beginning to wonder if this stupid hole even
has a bottom. *Sigh* You continue to climb down.

rooms.Name: Bottom of the Hole
rooms.Description:
Thank you Lord!!! You've finally made it to the bottom. You wipe the beads of
sweat from your forehead only to look up and see 2 of the biggest, meanest,
and ugliest monsters you've seen yet. This is not gonna be pretty. You take
firm hold of your weapon and utter a small prayer as the monsters lunge at
you.....

rooms.Name: Chamber of the Monster Queen
rooms.Description:
You are inside a huge chamber. Skeletons are lying about all over. This room
gives off the very air of death. In the middle of the chamber you can just
barely make out the outline of another monster, only this one is about 3
times the size of the rest of them. Damn, and you thought those last 2 were
ugly....

rooms.Name: A Walkway In the Trees
rooms.Description:
You stand on a sturdy looking wooden walkway built into tree tops. The
walkway seems to be held together and fastened to the trees by thick ropes.
You dont see anyone around. From here the walkway continues east, then bends
around a large tree. You can see footprints of dirt on the walkway, and they
look fresh. Someone must have been here recently.

Exits.Description:
You see a trap door in the floor of the walkway here, if you hadn't looked,
you would hve never noticed it.

rooms.Name: Edge of the Woods
rooms.Description:
You standing right before the tree line at the edge of the Dark Woods. Light
filters through the trees, and for once in a long time, you can see without
the aid of a light. There are still no animals here, but you at least feel
safer knowing you can see everything around you. You wonder what is outside
the trees.

rooms.Name: Edge of Graven Field
rooms.Description:
You are standing on the edge of Graven Field. In front of you is a huge
stretch of tall grass that continues as far as you can see. You can't see
over the grass, but you know that Graven must be on the other side of it
somewhere. You can hear some animals in the grass. It looks friendly enough,
why don't you go explore it?

rooms.Name: Among the Blades of Long Grass
rooms.Description:
You are standing in shoulder high grass. You can't see anything through the
blades. You feel slightly disoriented, being not exactly sure which way you
came, and not exactly sure which way you are going. You keep moving though,
the grass has to end somewhere.

rooms.Name: Among the Blades of Long Grass
rooms.Description:
You are standing in shoulder high grass. You can't see anything through the
blades. You feel slightly disoriented, being not exactly sure which way you
came, and not exactly sure which way you are going. You keep moving though,

rooms.Name: Among the Blades of Long Grass
rooms.Description:
As you walk through the grass, your foot hits something on the ground. You
stoop down to see what it is, only to see a huge swarm of bees appear from
inside the hive you just kicked. They begin stinging you, either kill them or
run, your choice.

You are standing in shoulder high grass. You can't see anything through the
blades. You feel slightly disoriented, being not exactly sure which way you
came, and not exactly sure which way you are going. You keep moving though,
the grass has to end somewhere.

rooms.Name: Path to Graven
rooms.Description:
You find yourself on the beginning of the road to Graven. Small cobblestones
make up the road. They look very old and worn, though you doubt that many
people travel into the field you just came from. In the distance you can make
out the village of Graven, and beyond it, the high walls of Graven castle.
You see a few people on the road ahead of you, picking flowers from the grass
that borders the road.

rooms.Name: On a Walkway In the Trees
rooms.Description:
The walkway makes a bend around a huge oak tree here. It leads south into a
small structure resembling a gatehouse. You wonder if anyone is in there.
It's beginning to get kinda creepy with no one around. On the walkway here
too are footprints of the same kind as you spotted farther back on the
walkway.

rooms.Name: Guard Post of the Woodlanders
rooms.Description:
You are standing inside a small wooden fortification. From the inside you can
see there is a large oak door that can be shut in times of attack. Looking
around though, you distinctly notice the building has been recently
constructed. You also happen to notice the 4 guards here that you have
startled.

rooms.Name: On a Walkway in the Trees
rooms.Description:
You are outside on the wooden walkway again, only now you can see many
Woodlanders milling around. A few of them glance up and see you. They seem
mostly indifferant to your presence though a few of them smile when thy see
you, though they don't know you. This is obviously not a hateful people. The
walkway continues east from here.

rooms.Name: On a Walkway in the Trees
rooms.Description:
The walkway continues and you walk by the many inhabitants of the Woodlander
village. All the people seem to be so nice. You wish everyone you knew where
this happy to see you. The walkway still continues east, but to the south
east, you can make out a large structure built into a huge tree.

rooms.Name: Before a Dwelling in the Trees
rooms.Description:
You are standing just outside a massive building carved out of the inside of
a GIGANTIC tree. You peer into the cut out windows and see many many rows of
wooden beds. The tree itself seems to be as old as time. Just looking at it,
you realize this thing was probably here when man first hunted animals for
food, and it'll probably be here after man has blown themselves up. The
walkway veers off to the north here, and the entrance to the dwelling lies
south.

Exits.Description: You look at the door. It is made out of thatch and looks pretty light.

rooms.Name: A Woodlander Dwelling
rooms.Description:
You are standing inside the tree. As you saw from outside, beds fill the huge
room, many of them occupied. In the back of room there appears to be a dining
area, and some sort of kitchen. There are many Woodlanders walking about in
here. Again you notice their lack of concern for your presence. The door back
outside lies to the north.

Exits.Description: You look at the door. It is made out of thatch and looks pretty light.

rooms.Name: Intersection of Walkways
rooms.Description:
The walkway branches off in 3 direction here, east, west, and south. To the
west the walkway continues by another dwelling. To the east the walkway
becomes a little obscure and there are less people on it. To the south the
walkway continues up to a dwelling, and bends west.

rooms.Name: On an Obscure Walkway
rooms.Description:
The walkway here has very few people on it. The people who are on it look at
you. This is the first time you've seen any of the woodlanders do more than
acknowledge your presence. The walkway continues to the east.

rooms.Name: Before a Dwelling in the Trees
rooms.Description:
You are again standing in front of large structure built out of the inside of
a huge tree. Looking through the cut out windows, you can make out more rows
of beds. There seems to be slightly more activity inside this particular
dwelling. The walkway leads off to the west from this point. The door to the
dwelling is directly north of you.

Exits.Description: You look at the door. It is made out of thatch and looks pretty light.

rooms.Name: A Woodlander Dwelling
rooms.Description:
You are in a dwelling similar to the one south east of here. Beds line the
walls, and people are slowly walking around, oblivious to your presence. In
the back, there is a small kitchen area where some Woodlanders appear to
making themselves something to drink. You can identify what they are mixing
with the water to make it. Cofee. Boy couldn't you use some? The exit is to
the south of where you are standing.

Exits.Description: You look at the door. It is made out of thatch and looks pretty light.

rooms.Name: On a Walkway in the Trees
rooms.Description:
You standing on another segment of walkway, trees on either side. The
occasional Woodlander walks by you. There doesn't seem to be too many of them
out this way. You get the feeling you're pretty close to the other edge of
their village. The walkway bends to the north here.

rooms.Name: On a Walkway in the Trees
rooms.Description:
This strip of walkway seems to be pretty empty. You guess not to many people
actually leave the village. To the west, you can see another new looking
building, identical to the one you saw when you first entered the village.
There are probably some guards in it, just like the other one.

rooms.Name: Guard Post of the Woodlanders
rooms.Description:
Yep, it's another guard post. You nearly scared the heck of of the guards who
are here. I guess they are a bit jumpy. You see the outside door is standing
open. It appears to be very thick. A small thought crosses your mind. What
would these people do if there ever was a fire? You decide to keep it to
yourself. The outside door is the the north of here.

rooms.Name: On a Walkway in the Trees
rooms.Description:
This piece of walkway is all by itself. The only exit you can see, except the
way you came, is a trap door in the floor. You wonder what's down there.
Maybe you should give it a look.

Exits.Description: You look down to see a trap door in the floor of the walkway here.

rooms.Name: On An Obscure Walkway
rooms.Description:
The walkway bends south here. Again you notice the Woodlanders here looking
at you. Almost staring at you. You almost feel as if you've done something
wrong. You sure hope you haven't.

rooms.Name: Before a Large Dwelling
rooms.Description:
You are standing before the largest dwelling you've seen yet, only this one
doesn't seem to be for people to sleep in. You try to peer in through the
windows, but some kind of blinds made from leaves, blocks your view. Every
now and then, someone opens the door and walks down the walkway, or does the
opposite, but they all give you a look. The door to the dwelling is west of
here.

Exits.Description:
This door is also made out of thatch, but it appears a lot stronger then the
others you've seen so far.

rooms.Name: Dwelling of the Woodlander Elder
rooms.Description:
You standing inside the huge dwelling. There are no beds, no kitchen, just a
large open space, and an old man sitting in the middle. You see a few
Woodlanders tending to his needs. He looks at you. He looks so incredibly
old. He is obviously the elder of the village, and probably it's leader. He
smiles at you. You feel a bit relieved. He seems to very nice. Maybe you
should say "hi"?
